🧠 Priority Reweighting System (PRS)

How humans override default reactions under pressure

⸻

🧭 Core Principle

You don’t remove fear—you change what outranks it.

Fear is still there.

But something else becomes stronger:
	•	mission
	•	protection
	•	identity
	•	training

⸻

⚙️ What’s actually happening (biologically + mentally)

1. Default State
	•	Brain prioritizes:
	•	survival
	•	safety
	•	Fear = dominant signal

⸻

2. Training / Conditioning

Repeated exposure + framing:
	•	loud noises → normalized
	•	chaos → familiar
	•	stress → expected

👉 Fear signal weakens relative to others

⸻

3. Priority Override

In critical moments:
	•	Value signal spikes (protect, act, complete mission)
	•	It outranks fear

So behavior becomes:

Action despite fear—not absence of fear

⸻

🧬 Your Bear Example (clean version)

Not:

“fear disappears”

But:

“protection instinct outranks self-preservation”

The system reprioritizes:

Signal	Weight (Normal)	Weight (Crisis)
Self-preservation	High	Lower
Protection (child)	Medium	Extreme
Fear response	High	Still present but overridden


